Chairman Senate Committee on Customs, Excise and Tariff, Senator Francis Alimikhena has withdrawn from the All Progressives Congress (APC) race in Edo North He also announced his resignation from the party. Senator Alimikhena in a letter he addressed to the National Chairman of the APC, Senator Abdullahi Adamu, said his decision was as due to injustice meted out to him by the party. The terse letter dated May 27, 2022, reads: “I write to notify you that I have withdrawn from the primary election as a result of injustice and also withdraw my membership of the All Progressives Congress (APC).”   Akure lawmaker loses re-election bid as thugs snatch ballot…     Okorocha to EFCC: drop charges against me     Two Ekiti Rep members secure tickets as one loses return bid   Ailimikhena has been having a running battle with a former National Chairman of APC, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole, over the Edo North Senatorial seat. Former Senate Deputy Ike Ekweremadu also denied he has joined the Labour Party (LP) as widely reported by many media organisations . In a statement by his media aide, Uche Anichukwu, Ekeremadu said the reports were false. The lawmaker, who withdrew from the governorship race in Enugu State, in a statement explained: “Our attention has been drawn to an online misinformation to the effect that former Deputy President of the Senate, Senator Ike Ekweremadu, has joined the Labour Party. “This is false and should be disregarded.”